-- Vettel Wins Korean Grand Prix Pole as Red Bull Team Continues to Dominate
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-10-23T13:34:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-23/vettel-wins-korean-grand-prix-pole-as-red-bull-team-continues-to-dominate.html
Sebastian Vettel won pole position
for tomorrow’s Korean Grand Prix, continuing the Red Bull team’s
dominance of Formula One qualifying.  Vettel edged teammate Mark Webber, the series leader, for
his second straight pole and ninth of the season. It was the
second consecutive 1-2 qualifying finish for Red Bull, which has
started from pole in 13 of the 16 races this season.  Ferrari’s Fernando Alonso will start third next to
McLaren’s Lewis Hamilton. Alonso and Vettel are tied for second
in the season standings, 14 points behind Webber.  Mercedes’s Nico Rosberg, Ferrari’s Felipe Massa, McLaren’s
Jenson Button, Renault’s Robert Kubica, Mercedes’s Michael
Schumacher and Williams’s Rubens Barichello round out the top 10
qualifiers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  